<%- include partials/header.ejs %>

<h1 class="display-3"><svg class="custom-icon"><use xlink:href="/assets/icons/icons.svg#steam_logo"></use></svg> Steam Randomizer</h1>

<div class="container">
<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1 class="display-5">Randomize a Game</h1>
    <p>Have tons of games in your steam library but don't still don't know what to play? We can give you a hand with that! Steam Randomizer uses only publicly available Steam Profile information to help you choose a random game to play from the ones you own.</p>
    <p>To get started, insert your public 
        <strong><span class="hint" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="top" title="Finding your Steam ID" data-html="true" data-content="This is not your Steam nickname or username, but the link to your community profile page. It should look like this: <strong>http://steamcommunity.com/id/yournamehere/</strong><br><strong>https://steamcommunity.com/profiles/7235162853115</strong>">Steam Profile ID, URL, or Custom URL <svg class="custom-icon"><use xlink:href="/assets/icons/icons.svg#help"></use></svg></span></strong> 
        in the box below, click Randomize and receive a random game instantly!</p>
    <form action="/randomize" method="GET">
        <div class="input-group justify-content-center">
            <span class="input-group-addon">Profile ID or URL</span>
            <input type="text" class="form-control" id="idInput" name="id" required>
        </div>
        <div class="input-group justify-content-center">
            <span class="input-group-addon">Maximum Playtime</span>
            <input type="number" class="form-control" id="minutesInput" name="min" placeholder="60">
            <span class="input-group-addon">Minutes</span>
        </div>
        <br>
        <hr>
        <h1 id="gauntlet_title" class="display-5">Achievement Gauntlet <svg class="custom-icon"><use xlink:href="/assets/icons/icons.svg#down_arrow"></use></svg></h1>
        <div id="gauntlet_div">
            <p>Want an extra challenge? Enable the options below to play in the <strong>Achievement Gauntlet <span>BETA</span></strong>! 
            Along with the random game, you get a random achievement (from the ones you haven't completed yet), which you must complete before 
            moving on to the next game. The difficulty is based on the global steam stats, calculated using the 
            <strong><span class="hint" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="top" title="Difficulty Settings" data-html="true" data-content="Distributed as follows:<br><strong>Easy</strong> - >30% of all players<br><strong>Medium</strong> - 15% to 30% of all players<br><strong>Hard</strong> - 5% to 15% of all players<br><strong>Expert</strong> - Less than 5% of all players">total percentage of players <svg class="custom-icon"><use xlink:href="/assets/icons/icons.svg#help"></use></svg></span></strong>
            that have completed each achievement. You may (and should) select more than one difficulty setting to customize your experience.</p>
            <br>
            <h4>Choose difficulties</h4>
            <div class="input-group justify-content-center">
                <span class="input-group-addon diffLabel">Easy<input type="checkbox" name="chk_easy"></span>
                <span class="input-group-addon diffLabel">Medium<input type="checkbox" name="chk_medium" checked></span>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group justify-content-center">
                <span class="input-group-addon diffLabel">Hard<input type="checkbox" name="chk_hard" checked></span>
                <span class="input-group-addon diffLabel">Expert<input type="checkbox" name="chk_expert"></span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <br>
        <div class="form-group">
            <button id="submit-btn" class="d-flex btn btn-primary"><svg class="custom-icon-btn"><use xlink:href="/assets/icons/icons.svg#dice"></use></svg>Randomize</button>
        </div>
    </form>
    
</div>
</div>

<%- include partials/footer.ejs %>
<script src="scripts/home.js"></script>
</body>
</html>